# Textbook Content Rules

- Render content from Firestore `contentBlocks`, not static files.
- Use `ContentBlockRenderer` for all block types.
- Markdown content uses `react-markdown` with `remark-gfm`.
- Each chapter follows the standard structure (Opening Case, Managerial Problem, Core Concepts, etc.).
- Block types: heading, paragraph, image, figure, table, quote, callout, research_box, case, quiz, ai_exercise, checklist, reference.
- Research boxes display "What Research Tells Us" header.
- Case blocks display "Case Study" header.
- AI exercises display "AI Exercise" header with distinct styling.
